        <!--NOTES! -----
            The backgrounds of the top and bottom images use the "luminosity" filter to harmonize the image's colors to the bootstrap theme. 
            
            To change the color, change bg-success to bg-primary, bg-warning, bg-danger, bg-info, bg-secondary, bg-dark, or bg-light.
            You can also remove bg-success and write next to class="" | style="background-color:#" | to give a custom color.
            
            To remove the effect, delete "luminosity" on line 33. 
            The background color won't effect the image unless it has a filter or is opaque (opacity:decimalnumber)
        --------------->
        
